## Icon Source Priority
1. **Figma SVG export** — product illustrations (Card Machine, Sound Box, Connect Plus)
2. **`Icons.tsx` library** — generic UI icons (check, close, arrows, etc.)
3. **Lucide React** — supplementary icons only (`ChevronRight`, `ArrowRight`, `X`, `ChevronDown`)
4. **Imported SVG paths** (`src/imports/`) — legacy Paytm brand icons (logo, sidebar nav)

## Rules

### DO
- Use `currentColor` for all stroke and fill values (except `white` body fills)
- Use `viewBox` for scalability — never set fixed `width`/`height` in SVG attributes
- Size via Tailwind: `className="size-6"`, `className="size-10"`, etc.
- Use `fill="none"` on the root `<svg>` element
- Add `strokeLinecap="round"` and `strokeLinejoin="round"` for clean line ends
- Keep product icons at `size-10` (40×40) with `viewBox="0 0 32 32"`
- Keep UI icons at `size-6` (24×24) with `viewBox="0 0 24 24"`
- Wrap icons in a background container (`bg-[#e0f5fd] rounded-[8px]`) for card contexts

### DO NOT
- Hardcode hex colors in SVG paths — use `currentColor` or `white` only
- Use `#00b8f5`, `#004299`, or `#101010` directly inside SVGs — use `currentColor` instead
- Mix icon sizing conventions — stick to the category sizes above
- Use raster/bitmap `<image>` inside SVGs — vector paths only
- Add `width` or `height` attributes to the `<svg>` element — use `className` sizing
- Create icons smaller than `size-5` (20px) for touch targets
- Use Lucide React icons when a matching icon exists in `Icons.tsx`
